Sentencas: A metal-supported solid oxide fuel cell (MS-SOFC) is fabricated by co-firing stainless steel (STS) support with a new reduction-resistant oxide-anode and yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte.
Titulo: Stainless steel-supported solid oxide fuel cell with La0.2Sr0.8Ti0.9Ni0.1O3-δ/yttria-stabilized zirconia composite anode

Sentencas: La and Ni co-doped SrTiO3 (La0.2Sr0.8Ti0.9Ni0.1O3-delta, LSTN) which shows Ni exsolution capability is composited with Y0.16Zr0.84O2-delta (YSZ) electrolyte to form a new LSTN-YSZ anode.
Titulo: Stainless steel-supported solid oxide fuel cell with La0.2Sr0.8Ti0.9Ni0.1O3-δ/yttria-stabilized zirconia composite anode

Sentencas: A cermet layer composed of STS and YSZ (STS-YSZ) is inserted between a porous STS support and a new LSTN-YSZ composite anode for stable contact.
Titulo: Stainless steel-supported solid oxide fuel cell with La0.2Sr0.8Ti0.9Ni0.1O3-δ/yttria-stabilized zirconia composite anode

Sentencas: With La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) cathode and Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta (GDC) interlayer coated on top of co-fired half-cell, YSZ/LSTN-YSZ/STS-YSZ/STS, a newly designed and fabricated cell achieved maximum power density of 185 mW cm(-2) at 650 degrees C.
Titulo: Stainless steel-supported solid oxide fuel cell with La0.2Sr0.8Ti0.9Ni0.1O3-δ/yttria-stabilized zirconia composite anode

Sentencas: This power density is an improvement over many conventional co-fired MS-SOFCs that use a Ni-cermet anode.
Titulo: Stainless steel-supported solid oxide fuel cell with La0.2Sr0.8Ti0.9Ni0.1O3-δ/yttria-stabilized zirconia composite anode
